@balloonym4 @Btshugbts @hiitsarpita @DIORlattae Of course, every road has their bumps some are just harsher than others. When you find the right ppl tho, they can make it a lot easier to go through with. It’s easy to get lost in this sea of chaos alone. But it’s okay to ask questions and look for help.

And if it really comes down to it, then you can also leave twt. When you do find the community that’s right for you it’s cool and fun but don’t force yourself into it.

@sujivenus Of course, if you ever need a ranting session or advise or just wanna talk you can just dm me if you’re ever comfortable with it.🥺💕

@sujivenus Having off days and days that feel like they drag on too long is okay but remember that each step you take no matter how small or big it is, it’s still a step. And no matter how many bad days you have, they don’t take away from what you’ve accomplished.

@sujivenus Yeah I get that,tho it’s best to remember that even “normal” ppl no matter who they are will be making mistakes all through their lives. No human is perfect and it’s our imperfections that makes us who we are. It’s hard to rmbr and takes time but knowing that will help a lot.

@sujivenus I bet, having to battle yourself and how you feel and then every other emotion or feeling that a disorder of yours may be feeling especially the most irrational ones can’t be an easy job. But the fact that you realize things you need to work on and are trying takes great effort.

@sujivenus Yeah, locking away apart of yourself especially something as big as ones emotions is hard, to spend so much time training your brain to do one thing  and then to suddenly stop doesn’t work and takes great effort to do. But slowly working on yourself is great and is a huge step.

@sujivenus Yeah, I can understand that. Our minds resorts to what we know best and it’ll do what it thinks is best to protect ourselves even if it’s not the best route. Working with one disorder is hard but fighting multiple is a lot more work and can make your disorders clash so to speak.
